  2020 AI & INNOVANow Calling for Papers!Artificial Intelligence is based on the research of fundamental and applied sciences. Through the evolution of information and engineering, it has gradually penetrated and changed not only our lives but our work style, which has resulted in bringing new experiences and convenience. And yet were facing with an unprecedented challenge and a crisis of privacy.An agenda, such diversified and interdisciplinary, ACEAI and the 8th ISFAS are honored to release the call under the theme Engineering and Information and Fundamental & Applied Sciences. We bring together interested parties from academia, consultancy and the public and private sectors in the beautiful city of Taipei.Highlight SpeechJohnson HuangSmart HealthcareFounder and General Manager of AdvMedsJohnson Huang is a serial entrepreneur who has won many awards of entrepreneurial competitions. With years of experience in the development and promotion of medical systems, he has participated in the national electronic medical record program, served as an IT consultant for hospitals and NGOs, and has been developing AIDS electronic information systems in Africa for several years.Topics Artificial Intelligence 5G Blockchain Internet of Things Engineering InformationFundamental Sciences Applied SciencesSubmit NowMark your Calendar Submission Deadline: February 05, 2020 Notification of Acceptance: From February 19, 2020 Registration Deadline: March 30, 2020 Conference Date  June 01 -04, 2020Contact & InquiriesACEAI
